title: 17.351 DEFINITIONS.
text:
The definitions in this section apply to sections 17.352 to 17.354.
[Repealed, 1996 c 310 s 1]
"Fur-bearing animal" means a fox, mink, fitch, chinchilla, karakul, marten, nutria, or fisher that is the second or later generation raised in captivity.
"Fur farmer" means a person engaged in breeding, raising, producing, and marketing fur-bearing animals or the products of fur-bearing animals.
